## 14. Time Complexity

Let (n) be the number of students.

### Validation

```python
validate_students(students)
```

Checks every student once:

[
O(n)
]

### Average

```python
calculate_average(students)
```

Reads every score once:

[
O(n)
]

### Pass Rate

```python
calculate_pass_rate(students)
```

Checks every student once:

[
O(n)
]

### Grade Distribution

```python
build_grade_distribution(students)
```

Processes every student once:

[
O(n)
]

### Top Student

```python
find_top_student(students)
```

Searches every student:

[
O(n)
]

The program performs several separate (O(n)) operations:

[
O(n) + O(n) + O(n) + O(n) + O(n)
]

Constants are ignored in Big-O notation:

[
O(5n) = O(n)
]

Therefore, the overall time complexity is:

[
\boxed{O(n)}
]

The grade-distribution dictionary always contains five grades, so its additional space complexity is:

[
\boxed{O(1)}
]

The input dataset itself requires:

[
O(n)
]

space.

